a.xlink:title: Preparation/bringing to market of a security (also known as primary market or Initial Public Offering (IPO) issuance).
Specifies the value expressed as a rate or an amount. For example, the value of a tax or a commission.
An event determined by a corporation's board of directors, that changes the existing corporate capital structure or financial condition.
Tangible items of value to a business.
Characteristics related to the price of the security.
Context or geographic environment in which trading parties may meet in order to negotiate and execute trades among themselves. It also identifies the primary market where an asset is issued.
Amount of money targeted to be raised through the issuance of a security.
Time span defined by a start date and time, and an end date and time.
